🖥️ Linux System Health Report Automation
A Bash script that automates system health monitoring by collecting important Linux server metrics such as CPU, memory, disk usage, uptime, running services, logged-in users, and top resource-consuming processes.
The script generates a daily health report, saves it to a log file, and can be scheduled using Cron to run automatically every day.
---
# Project Overview
Monitoring server health is one of the routine operational tasks performed by DevOps and SRE engineers.
This project automates the collection of system health information using Shell Scripting and Linux utilities.
The generated report can be used for:
- Daily server health checks
- Preventive maintenance
- Capacity planning
- Troubleshooting
- Infrastructure monitoring
- Operations reporting
---
